    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Registration/12–1444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-14T08:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 14, 1944—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2017. Final date for registration of foreign companies extended to June 30, 1945
                    (ReEmbs 1959, December 6, 10 a.m.<note n="44" xml:id="d748fn44">Not
                        printed.</note>). In letter of December 11 advising Embassy of extension,
                    Economic Affairs Minister requests foreign business concerns be directed to make
                    effective preparations for fulfillment of registration procedure at early
                    date.</p>
                <p>Embassy requests transmission of memoranda from Councils (ReDepts 1494, November
                    16) be expedited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
